cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NA, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a variational multi-label segmentation algorithm for images. The use of a robust Huber loss and a regularization scheme also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The optimization algorithm used in the paper, based on the alternating direction method of multipliers, suggests that it could also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the empirical validation of the algorithm on synthetic and real images suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
